verses.verse: To the chief <S%H5329><s%> Musician, <S%H5329><s%> A Song <S%H7892><s%> or Psalm. <S%H4210><s%> Make a joyful noise to God, <S%H430><s%> all <S%H3605><s%> you lands: <S%H776><s%>
Sing <S%H2167><s%> forth the honor <S%H3519><s%> of his name: <S%H8034><s%> make <S%H7760><s%> his praise <S%H8416><s%> glorious. <S%H3519><s%>

Say <S%H559><s%> to God, <S%H430><s%> How <S%H4100><s%> terrible <S%H3372><s%> are you in your works! <S%H4639><s%> through the greatness <S%H7230><s%> of your power <S%H5797><s%> shall your enemies <S%H341><s%> submit <S%H3584><s%> themselves to you.
All <S%H3605><s%> the earth <S%H776><s%> shall worship <S%H7812><s%> you, and shall sing <S%H2167><s%> to you; they shall sing <S%H2167><s%> to your name. <S%H8034><s%> Selah. <S%H5542><s%>

Come <S%H3212><s%> and see <S%H7200><s%> the works <S%H4659><s%> of God: <S%H430><s%> he is terrible <S%H3372><s%> in his doing <S%H5949><s%> toward <S%H5921><s%> the children <S%H1121><s%> of men. <S%H120><s%>

He turned <S%H2015><s%> the sea <S%H3220><s%> into dry <S%H3004><s%> land: <S%H776><s%> they went <S%H5674><s%> through the flood <S%H5104><s%> on foot: <S%H7272><s%> there <S%H8033><s%> did we rejoice <S%H8055><s%> in him.

He rules <S%H4910><s%> by his power <S%H1369><s%> for ever; <S%H5769><s%> his eyes <S%H5869><s%> behold <S%H6822><s%> the nations: <S%H1471><s%> let not the rebellious <S%H5637><s%> exalt <S%H7311><s%> themselves. Selah. <S%H5542><s%>
O bless <S%H1288><s%> our God, <S%H430><s%> you people, <S%H5971><s%> and make the voice <S%H6963><s%> of his praise <S%H8416><s%> to be heard: <S%H8085><s%>
Which holds <S%H7760><s%> our soul <S%H5315><s%> in life, <S%H2416><s%> and suffers <S%H5414><s%> not our feet <S%H7272><s%> to be moved. <S%H4132><s%>
For you, O God, <S%H430><s%> have proved <S%H974><s%> us: you have tried <S%H6884><s%> us, as silver <S%H3701><s%> is tried. <S%H6884><s%>
You brought <S%H935><s%> us into the net; <S%H4685><s%> you laid <S%H7760><s%> affliction <S%H4157><s%> on our loins. <S%H4975><s%>

You have caused men <S%H582><s%> to ride <S%H7392><s%> over our heads; <S%H7218><s%> we went <S%H935><s%> through fire <S%H784><s%> and through water: <S%H4325><s%> but you brought <S%H3318><s%> us out into a wealthy <S%H7310><s%> place.
I will go <S%H935><s%> into your house <S%H1004><s%> with burnt <S%H5930><s%> offerings: I will pay <S%H7999><s%> you my vows, <S%H5088><s%>
Which <S%H834><s%> my lips <S%H8193><s%> have uttered, <S%H6475><s%> and my mouth <S%H6310><s%> has spoken, <S%H1696><s%> when I was in trouble. <S%H6862><s%>

I will offer <S%H5927><s%> to you burnt <S%H5930><s%> sacrifices of fatted calves, <S%H4220><s%> with the incense <S%H7004><s%> of rams; <S%H352><s%> I will offer <S%H6213><s%> bullocks <S%H1241><s%> with goats. <S%H6260><s%> Selah. <S%H5542><s%>

Come <S%H3212><s%> and hear, <S%H8085><s%> all <S%H3605><s%> you that fear <S%H3373><s%> God, <S%H430><s%> and I will declare <S%H5608><s%> what <S%H834><s%> he has done <S%H6213><s%> for my soul. <S%H5315><s%>
I cried <S%H7121><s%> to him with my mouth, <S%H6310><s%> and he was extolled <S%H7318><s%> with my tongue. <S%H3956><s%>
If <S%H518><s%> I regard <S%H7200><s%> iniquity <S%H205><s%> in my heart, <S%H3820><s%> the Lord <S%H136><s%> will not hear <S%H8085><s%> me:
But truly <S%H403><s%> God <S%H430><s%> has heard <S%H8085><s%> me; he has attended <S%H7181><s%> to the voice <S%H6963><s%> of my prayer. <S%H8605><s%>
Blessed <S%H1288><s%> be God, <S%H430><s%> which <S%H834><s%> has not turned <S%H5493><s%> away my prayer, <S%H8605><s%> nor his mercy <S%H2617><s%> from me.
